        <p>Our URL shortener service uses a Base62 encoding algorithm to generate short, unique URLs. Here's how it works:</p>
        
        <h3>1Encoding</h3>
        <p>We use Base62 encoding (using characters A-Z, a-z, and 0-9) because:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>It's URL-safe (no special characters)</li>
            <li>It's case-sensitive, allowing for more combinations</li>
            <li>It's human-readable and easy to share</li>
        </ul>

